{"name": "pdfocrer", "metadata": {"name": "PdfOCRer", "version": "1.1.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/msmarkgu/PdfOCRer", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pypdf2", "pillow", "reportlab", "paddleocr"], "summary": "A Python script that runs Paddle OCR on a possibly unsearchable PDF to make it searchable.", "upload_time": 1734500224}, "documentation": ["# PdfOCRer\n\nPdfOCRer is a python script that runs OCR on an input PDF (possibly unsearchable) to produce a searchable PDF.\n\nIt uses [Paddle OCR](https://paddlepaddle.github.io/PaddleOCR/latest/index.html) as the OCR engine. Compared to the famous OCR engine [Tesseract](https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tesseract), Paddle OCR shows better results for Chinese language in my experiments. However, it cannot seem to generate searchable PDF from its OCR result, whereas Tesseract can. If that's what you need, PdfOCRer can help.\n\nPdfOCRer processes a PDF in four steps:\n\n- Step 1: convert each pdf page into an image (default format PNG).\n- Step 2: run OCR on each image to recognize text and bounding boxes.\n- Step 3: add text/bbox on image as hidden layer to make 1-page PDF.\n- Step 4: merge all 1-page pdfs to output the result searchable pdf.\n\n# Dependencies\n\nThe script is tested in Python 3.10. It should work as long as the dependencies work.\n\n- Paddle OCR: follow its instruction [here](https://paddlepaddle.github.io/PaddleOCR/latest/ppocr/quick_start.html).\n\n- PyPDF2, Pillow, ReportLab: ``` pip install pillow PyPDF2 reportlab ```\n\n- Ghostscript: used to convert pdf to images, called from the script as subprocess. \n\n    -- on Linux/Ubuntu: ``` apt-get install ghostscript ```, \n\n    -- on MacOS machine: ``` brew install ghostscript ```.\n\n# How to use\n\nOpen a terminal, run the script like following:\n\n```\npython pdf_ocrer.py -i <input_pdf> -o <output_pdf> -l <language> -t <temp_dir> [--debug]\n```\n\nExample:\n\n```\npython pdf_ocrer.py -i ../example/scanned_page.pdf -o ../example/scanned_page.ocr.pdf -t ../temp -l ch --debug\n```\n\n# Acknowledgement\n\nThanks to the authors of all the depencenies libraries, the Python and Open Source Community.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "src.pdf_util", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "src.pdf_util.RootLogger", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "src.pdf_util.RootLogger.printInfo", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "message", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "src.pdf_util.RootLogger.getLogger", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "logger_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "debug", "type": {"name": "False", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.False", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "logging.Logger", "xref": {"fqname": "logging.Logger", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "src.pdf_util.PdfUtil", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "src.pdf_util.PdfUtil.get_total_pages", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pdf_path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "src.pdf_util.PdfUtil.get_page_dimension", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pdf_path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "page_num", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": n